The paper discusses the use of neural networks and analogue computing, which are both topics commonly found in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The paper also focuses on the use of physical media for error backpropagation, which falls under the cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) sub-category. The use of reciprocal linear dynamical systems with nonlinear feedback is a topic that can be found in the cs.EM (Electromagnetics) sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential scalability of neuro-inspired hardware, which falls under the cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of dynamical analogue computers, which can be found in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
